## 2. 🔒 SSL/HTTPS Configuration

### Vercel (Client & Admin)
Vercel auto-provisions SSL via Let's Encrypt. Ensure:
- Custom domain is added in **Vercel Dashboard → Domains**
- HTTPS is enforced by default — no extra config needed

### Render (Server/API)
Render also auto-provisions SSL. In your `render.yaml` or dashboard:
- Ensure your service uses HTTPS endpoint (e.g., `https://your-app.onrender.com`)
- Force HTTPS in your Node.js app:

```javascript
// server/index.js or app.js
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  if (req.headers['x-forwarded-proto'] !== 'https' && process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production') {
    return res.redirect(301, 'https://' + req.headers.host + req.url);
  }
  next();
});
```

### Nginx (if self-hosting)
```bash
# Install Certbot
sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx -y
sudo certbot --nginx -d yourdomain.com -d www.yourdomain.com

# Auto-renew (add to crontab)
0 3 * * * certbot renew --quiet
```

```nginx
# nginx.conf — Force HTTPS
server {
  listen 80;
  server_name yourdomain.com www.yourdomain.com;
  return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
}
```

